 She walks over to the table. 
"This is for you." he says, pointing at the cup.
  "What about you?" she asks. "Don't you want a drink too?" 
"Oh, I don't need one." he replies.
 "I just had one last week." "That's odd," she thought. She tried to think of something to say. 
"Oh, so do you come here often?" she asks.
 
"I come here every week." he replies.
 She was confused. 

"I thought you said you just had a drink here last week." she says. She was wondering if she should leave. 
"I did." he says.
 At this point, it didn't matter. She was ready to go. 
"Well, I gotta run.

He sat back down.

A woman has been dating guy after guy, but it never seems to work out. She’s unaware that she’s actually been dating the same guy over and over; a shapeshifter who’s fallen for her, and is certain he’s going to get it right this time.
